<Project Sdk="Dalamud.NET.Sdk/15.0.0">

  <PropertyGroup>
    <Author>LastOnionKnight</Author>
    <Name>Tonberry Tactics</Name>
    <InternalName>GearGoblin</InternalName>
    <AssemblyVersion>0.6.5.3</AssemblyVersion>
    <FileVersion>0.6.5.3</FileVersion>
    <Version>0.6.5.3</Version>
    <MinimumDalamudVersion>15.0.0</MinimumDalamudVersion>
    <Punchline>BiS planner, Materia Advisor, and round-trip optimizer for FFXIV. The in-game half of Tonberry Tactics; coexists with CharacterPanelRefined.</Punchline>
    <Description>The in-game half of Tonberry Tactics — BiS planner, gear inventory reader, materia advisor for FFXIV. v0.6.5.3 ("Collision Fix") corrects the character-panel ghost-text bug that v0.6.5.2 misdiagnosed. The Materia Advisor section injected under "Average Item Level" rendered with ghost-text overlay artifacts on the "Materia Advisor" header line, visible on every job's Character window (VPR/PLD combat panels and CRP crafter panel were the test cases). v0.6.5.2 attempted a fix by pre-padding the Gear component's parent + collision node by 20px before the first advisor row — that approach grew the collision node, which is exactly the operation that causes the ghost text. Going back to the CharacterPanelRefined upstream we adapted from surfaced the right pattern: AddStatRow needs an "expandCollisionNode" parameter, and the Gear / Average Item Level / Crafter-stats rows must pass false to suppress collision growth while still growing the parent component's height for visible space. v0.6.5.3 adds that parameter to our AddStatRow, removes the v0.6.5.2 pre-pad block, and passes expandCollisionNode: false to all 4 advisor row injections. Same release also lands the brand-convergence fixes the v0.5.x sweep missed in this file: advisor pill text reads "▶ /tt" instead of "▶ /goblin" (both empty and with-audits branches), and clicking the pill invokes /tt instead of /goblin. Companion web (TonberryTactics v0.6.5.3) and Core (GearGoblin.Core v0.6.5.3) are version-only lockstep bumps with no source changes.</Description>
    <RepoUrl>https://github.com/LastOnionKnight/GearGoblin</RepoUrl>
    <Tags>gear;bis;materia;etro;xivgear;raid;advisor;cpr;character-panel;tonberry-tactics</Tags>

    <Nullable>enable</Nullable>
    <LangVersion>latest</LangVersion>
    <AllowUnsafeBlocks>true</AllowUnsafeBlocks>
  </PropertyGroup>

  <!-- v0.4.7.1: brand artwork shipped alongside the DLL. Dalamud's SDK
       picks these up automatically via the Content glob and includes them
       in the plugin's install directory; runtime resolves via
       PluginInterface.AssemblyLocation.Directory + "Assets/" (see
       Services/BrandResources.cs). -->
  <ItemGroup>
    <Content Include="Assets\**\*.png">
      <CopyToOutputDirectory>PreserveNewest</CopyToOutputDirectory>
      <Pack>true</Pack>
    </Content>
  </ItemGroup>

  <!-- v0.6.0: custom .ttf fonts for IFontAtlas Phase 2. Same copy
       discipline as the brand artwork — runtime resolves the directory
       via PluginInterface.AssemblyLocation.Directory + "Assets/Fonts/"
       (see Theme/FontAtlasManager.cs). -->
  <ItemGroup>
    <Content Include="Assets\Fonts\*.ttf">
      <CopyToOutputDirectory>PreserveNewest</CopyToOutputDirectory>
      <Pack>true</Pack>
    </Content>
  </ItemGroup>

  <!--
    v0.6.3: ProjectReference to the shared GearGoblin.Core library.
    Path assumes the standard sibling-of-grandparent layout:

        D:\GearGoblin-Core-v0.1\GearGoblin.Core\        (Core, this reference's target)
        D:\GearGoblin-v0.1\GearGoblin\                  (this project)
        D:\TonberryTactics-workspace\TonberryTactics\   (web, mirrors this same reference)

    If Core lives somewhere else on your machine, update the path to
    point at your local clone. The web's csproj uses the same relative
    pattern so both halves resolve to the same library on disk.

    Plugin's existing MeldOptimizer (already job-aware via JobProfile)
    continues to function unchanged in v0.6.3 — Core integration on
    the plugin side is incremental, tracked for v0.7.x alongside the
    CPR-replacement work. Today's ProjectReference exists so future
    migrations are mechanical rather than gated on adding a dependency.
  -->
  <ItemGroup>
    <ProjectReference Include="..\..\GearGoblin-Core-v0.1\GearGoblin.Core\GearGoblin.Core.csproj" />
  </ItemGroup>

</Project>
